## How each mandatory security requirement is met

| Requirement | Implementation |
|---|---|
| SQL injection | PDO **prepared statements** everywhere; `ATTR_EMULATE_PREPARES => false` |
| Password hashing | `password_hash()` with **Argon2id**, bcrypt fallback (build-detected via `password_algos()`); per-hash salt managed by PHP |
| Input validation/sanitisation | Length/charset/format checks + control-char stripping for name, message, username, password |
| Output encoding (XSS) | `e()` = `htmlspecialchars(ENT_QUOTES)` on every rendered value + strict CSP with no inline scripts |
| CSRF | Synchronizer token on all POSTs, verified with `hash_equals()`, checked centrally |
| Access control / IDOR | Delete loads the row and verifies `user_id` ownership (or admin) **server-side** before acting |
| Session cookies | `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, configurable `Secure`; `session_regenerate_id()` on login; strict mode |
| Security headers | `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, `Referrer-Policy`, `Permissions-Policy`, CSP, optional HSTS |
| No error leakage | Custom handlers log server-side, return generic message; `display_errors` off in production |
| No hardcoded secrets | `APP_KEY`/DB path/admin seed read from env/`.env`; refuses to boot in production with the default key |

