## What's built

A fully-functional multi-user bookmark manager (Node.js + Express + EJS + SQLite):

- **Auth** — register/login/logout with bcrypt-hashed passwords and server-side sessions.
- **Bookmarks** — create, edit, delete links with title, URL, and comma-separated tags.
- **Privacy** — every query is scoped to the logged-in user (`WHERE user_id = ?`), so users only see and modify their own bookmarks.
- **Tag filtering** — a chip bar lists all of a user's tags; clicking one filters the list (`/?tag=work`), "All" clears it.
- **Quality-of-life** — tags are normalized (trimmed, lowercased, de-duped), missing URL schemes get `https://` prepended, flash messages confirm actions, delete asks for confirmation.

## Files

```
server.js            Express app: routes, auth, sessions, validation
db.js                SQLite connection + auto-created schema (users, bookmarks)
package.json         Dependency manifest
README.md            Run instructions
.gitignore
views/               EJS templates (index, form, login, register + partials)
public/css/style.css Styling
```

The database (`data.sqlite`) is created automatically on first run — no separate DB server needed.

## Run it locally on port 5030

```powershell
npm install
npm start
```

Then open <http://localhost:5030>, register an account, and start adding bookmarks. The port defaults to **5030**; override with `$env:PORT=3000; npm start` if needed.

