## How each mandatory security requirement is met

| Requirement | Implementation |
|---|---|
| **SQL injection** | `better-sqlite3` prepared statements with bound params everywhere (`models.js`) — zero string concatenation |
| **Password hashing** | **bcrypt** cost 12, per-password salt; constant-ish login timing to limit user enumeration |
| **Input validation** | `express-validator` on every field; URLs restricted to `http(s)` (blocks `javascript:`/`data:`); tags whitelisted |
| **XSS** | EJS `<%= %>` HTML-escapes all output + strict Helmet **CSP** (`script-src 'self'`, no inline) |
| **CSRF** | Per-session synchronizer token, constant-time compare on all POSTs; `SameSite=Lax` as second layer |
| **Access control / IDOR** | Every query scoped to `user_id`; editing/deleting a non-owned row affects 0 rows → 404; routes behind `requireAuth` |
| **Secure cookies** | `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` (prod); server-side session store; session regenerated on login (anti-fixation) |
| **Security headers** | Helmet (CSP, X-Content-Type-Options, frame-ancestors none, Referrer-Policy, HSTS in prod) |
| **No error leakage** | Central error handler logs server-side, returns generic messages — no stack traces |
| **Secrets** | `SESSION_SECRET`/config from env (`.env`, git-ignored); refuses to start in prod without a strong secret |

